She even secretly gifted him a handkerchief where she stitched his initials and flowers onto it.

259
00:19:35,130 --> 00:19:40,040
All this time, Ms. Park was seducing the Chairman behind our backs.

260
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:43,790
Oh, my! How could she be so sly?!

261
00:19:43,790 --> 00:19:47,330
But why haven't you said anything about this to me until now?

262
00:19:47,330 --> 00:19:51,360
I also had a hard time believing it.

263
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:55,090
I thought it was ridiculous...

264
00:19:55,090 --> 00:19:58,570
Also, you were upset about Ms. Se Ryun.

265
00:19:58,570 --> 00:20:01,510
I can't add to that.

266
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:07,710
Seriously, you're just too nice.

267
00:20:07,710 --> 00:20:10,850
The way that the Chairman looks at Ms. Park is strange.

268
00:20:10,850 --> 00:20:13,970
I think that the Chairman...

269
00:20:13,970 --> 00:20:17,330
may be falling for Ms. Park...

270
00:20:17,330 --> 00:20:18,960
What do I do?

271
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:25,330
What do you mean by that? We have to nip it in the bud immediately! We have to kick her out now!

272
00:20:25,330 --> 00:20:26,910
Pardon?

273
00:20:26,910 --> 00:20:29,640
Chief Jo. What did I tell you?

274
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:34,040
In my heart, you're already my daughter-in-law, Chief Jo!

275
00:20:34,040 --> 00:20:36,860
But, do you think I'll do nothing after seeing something like this?

276
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:39,180
Don't even worry about it. I'll take care of everything.

277
00:20:39,180 --> 00:20:42,560
Getting rid of a little girl like her is not even a problem.

278
00:20:42,560 --> 00:20:46,480
Why are you even worried about a nobody like her?

279
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:49,370
Madam...

280
00:20:51,710 --> 00:20:54,860
Mother-in-law...

281
00:21:12,630 --> 00:21:18,120
Why is grandma going into Ms. Park's room?

282
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:21,530
Ms. Park's not even home.

283
00:21:49,610 --> 00:21:53,120
Joon Oh, are you leaving already?

284
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:55,400
Do you want me to drive to the Seoul Train Station?

285
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:58,690
Am I a child? I'm going to go with my friend.

286
00:21:58,690 --> 00:22:02,640
My son, when am I going to see you again?

287
00:22:02,640 --> 00:22:06,130
At least call me often, okay?

288
00:22:06,130 --> 00:22:09,420
Mom, I will come home every weekend from now on.

289
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:13,060
What? Am I going to see you every weekend?

290
00:22:13,060 --> 00:22:15,660
- Really?
- Yes.

291
00:22:15,660 --> 00:22:19,430
Doctor, I'll see you later.

292
00:22:19,430 --> 00:22:21,220
I'm not a doctor yet.

293
00:22:21,220 --> 00:22:23,570
Have a nice day.

294
00:22:23,570 --> 00:22:27,210
Hurry on. You have a train to catch.

295
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:37,570
Hey, what's going on?

296
00:22:37,570 --> 00:22:40,920
Do you need more allowance?

297
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:45,410
Mom, you trust me, right?

298
00:22:45,410 --> 00:22:48,090
Of course, I do.

299
00:22:48,090 --> 00:22:52,100
If I don't trust my son, who can I trust?

300
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:54,810
I will get going.

301
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:03,270
These are all almost new.

302
00:23:03,270 --> 00:23:05,840
Thank you for giving it to me.

303
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:10,810
Are you not going to tell your mom that you took the semester off?

304
00:23:14,750 --> 00:23:16,990
I should tell her.

305
00:23:16,990 --> 00:23:20,380
But I'm going to tell her later when I get my license.

306
00:23:20,380 --> 00:23:24,080
Are you going to get a license? I thought you were doing it for fun.

307
00:23:24,080 --> 00:23:28,020
Are you really going to be a hair designer or whatever?

308
00:23:28,020 --> 00:23:32,590
Don't tell me you're going to give up the medical school you worked so hard to get in.

309
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:37,440
I don't know.

310
00:23:39,310 --> 00:23:43,510
No more difficult question like that, please.

311
00:23:43,510 --> 00:23:47,040
We only live once.

312
00:23:47,050 --> 00:23:51,600
I want to find something that I want to do, have fun doing it,

313
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:54,810
something that suits me.

314
00:23:54,810 --> 00:23:57,880
I'm going to find that out.

315
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:05,820
That's the life's road map I've decided for myself.

316
00:24:05,820 --> 00:24:09,170
Okay, Bong Joon Oh. Good luck with that.

317
00:24:09,170 --> 00:24:12,390
And I hope you survive from your mom whenever you tell her.

318
00:24:12,390 --> 00:24:15,170
I got it.

319
00:24:15,170 --> 00:24:17,930
If I do become a hair designer,

320
00:24:17,930 --> 00:24:21,230
I will take charge of your hair.

321
00:24:21,230 --> 00:24:23,740
Okay.

322
00:24:35,710 --> 00:24:38,140
What's up with that guy?

323
00:24:38,140 --> 00:24:42,630
Did he register here because of me?

324
00:24:42,630 --> 00:24:45,530
Something is off.

325
00:24:55,480 --> 00:24:59,450
Chief Jo! Mrs. Yeoju, Chief Jo!

326
00:24:59,450 --> 00:25:02,270
- Yes, Madam.
- What's wrong, Madam?

327
00:25:02,270 --> 00:25:04,490
My necklace is gone.

328
00:25:04,490 --> 00:25:06,900
The necklace that I bought not long ago.

329
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:10,060
Do you mean the diamond necklace?

330
00:25:10,060 --> 00:25:13,050
Yes, that diamond necklace.

331
00:25:13,050 --> 00:25:15,770
Madam, I am sure we can find it somewhere.

332
00:25:15,770 --> 00:25:18,460
Please think carefully, where you left it.

333
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:22,610
What is there to think? I left it on top of my dresser this morning.

334
00:25:22,610 --> 00:25:24,610
But it's gone.

335
00:25:24,610 --> 00:25:26,490
I didn't see it when I was cleaning earlier.

336
00:25:26,490 --> 00:25:27,840
I will look for it again.

337
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:30,340
It's not there. I'm telling you!

338
00:25:30,340 --> 00:25:33,430
I looked at every nook and cranny!

339
00:25:33,430 --> 00:25:36,210
It's not like the necklace has legs or wings.

340
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:39,530
Unless someone took it, how would it disappear?

341
00:25:39,530 --> 00:25:43,920
Oh, my goodness. Are you saying someone stole it?

342
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:46,730
No, Madam. Why would anyone do that?

343
00:25:46,730 --> 00:25:50,020
Something like this has never happened in our house before.

344
00:25:50,020 --> 00:25:52,740
There is only one who came into our house recently.

345
00:25:52,740 --> 00:25:55,070
Mrs. Yeoju, you weren't here because you went to the market.

346
00:25:55,070 --> 00:25:59,060
I saw Ms. Park coming and going.

347
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:04,240
It cannot be Ms. Park!

348
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:06,620
Ah, seriously!

349
00:26:09,450 --> 00:26:11,650
What is going on?

350
00:26:11,650 --> 00:26:14,350
Why is she acting like that?

351
00:26:20,930 --> 00:26:23,160
Madam, I don't think this is right.

352
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:25,280
Ms. Park is not someone who would do something like that.

353
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:29,010
Then where would my necklace that was sitting on my dresser go?

354
00:26:29,010 --> 00:26:32,120
There is only one who's new to our house.

355
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:34,250
Help me find it, Mrs. Yeoju!

356
00:26:34,250 --> 00:26:36,250
But still, I don't think this is the right way.

357
00:26:36,250 --> 00:26:39,190
I don't think Ms. Park will stand for something like this.

358
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:43,640
Aigoo, what would she do if she didn't stand for it?

359
00:26:43,640 --> 00:26:47,080
Oh, my goodness. It's here, Madam.

360
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:51,780
This necklace is your diamond necklace, right?

361
00:26:51,780 --> 00:26:53,540
Yes, that's the one!

362
00:26:53,540 --> 00:26:56,170
This is the necklace that I lost.

363
00:26:56,170 --> 00:26:58,930
Yes. I knew it, I knew it!

364
00:26:58,930 --> 00:27:02,590
It sure looks like we raised a thieving wench.

365
00:27:02,590 --> 00:27:07,410
I didn't want to think it, but how could she do this?

366
00:27:07,410 --> 00:27:11,140
My goodness, this doesn't make any sense.

367
00:27:13,170 --> 00:27:17,910
Madam, Chief Jo, what are you all doing here?

368
00:27:17,910 --> 00:27:20,170
Ms. Park.

369
00:27:20,170 --> 00:27:24,340
Why is this necklace in your room?

370
00:27:24,340 --> 00:27:26,120
What is it?

371
00:27:26,120 --> 00:27:30,030
How can you play ignorant when we just found it in your drawer?

372
00:27:30,030 --> 00:27:32,660
We didn't bring in a live-in tutor,

373
00:27:32,660 --> 00:27:37,020
but a thieving wench!

374
00:27:37,020 --> 00:27:38,710
Madam.

375
00:27:38,710 --> 00:27:41,430
What are you saying?

376
00:27:41,430 --> 00:27:46,270
Why is Madam's lost diamond necklace in your drawer?

377
00:27:46,270 --> 00:27:49,430
Please explain how this happened.

378
00:27:49,430 --> 00:27:52,080
That was in my drawer?

379
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:53,620
Yes, it was.

380
00:27:53,620 --> 00:27:56,040
Both Madam and I saw it.

381
00:27:56,040 --> 00:27:59,740
And Mrs. Yeoju too, right?

382
00:27:59,740 --> 00:28:04,850
Ms. Park, what's going on?

383
00:28:04,850 --> 00:28:09,250
That can't be. I've never seen the necklace before.

384
00:28:09,250 --> 00:28:12,790
Madam, it's not me. Please believe me.

385
00:28:12,790 --> 00:28:15,880
What do you mean it's not you when there is proof?

386
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:20,200
Chief, Jo, I can't leave our children to a thieving wench like her. Please dismiss her immediately!

387
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:22,180
Kick her out now!

388
00:28:22,180 --> 00:28:25,330
What is going on right now?

389
00:28:25,330 --> 00:28:27,180
What did Ms. Park do?

390
00:28:27,180 --> 00:28:30,190
Chairman Lee! Young Gook.

391
00:28:30,190 --> 00:28:33,470
Ms. Park stole my necklace.

392
00:28:33,470 --> 00:28:37,760
Ms. Park is a thief. You must kick her out immediately!

393
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:41,780
I really didn't do it.

394
00:28:41,780 --> 00:28:45,620
How can you say it so thoughtlessly? She's saying she didn't do it.

395
00:28:45,620 --> 00:28:47,540
Listen, CEO Anna.

396
00:28:47,540 --> 00:28:51,370
The necklace I lost was in Ms. Park's drawer.

397
00:28:51,370 --> 00:28:56,710
Without knowing the details, why are you jumping in like that?

398
00:28:56,710 --> 00:28:59,480
Even so, you can't accuse someone only on that basis.

399
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:01,990
Ms. Park is not someone who would do something like that.

400
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:07,230
Okay then, did my necklace walk here on its own two feet?

401
00:29:07,230 --> 00:29:10,190
Anyway, you have to kick her out of the house immediately, Chairman Lee!

402
00:29:10,190 --> 00:29:15,360
No matter what, stealing cannot be tolerated, don't you agree?

403
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:19,270
I put that necklace there.

404
00:29:21,940 --> 00:29:24,350
Se Chan, did you put it there?

405
00:29:24,350 --> 00:29:26,770
Yes. I saw it on the kitchen floor,

406
00:29:26,770 --> 00:29:29,350
and I thought it belonged to Ms. Park.

407
00:29:29,350 --> 00:29:33,420
Se Chan! Oh, Se Chan.

408
00:29:33,420 --> 00:29:35,260
That's not possible.

409
00:29:35,260 --> 00:29:38,520
That can't be true.

410
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:41,720
Se Chan, you really put it there, right?

411
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:43,340
Yes, that's true!

412
00:29:43,340 --> 00:29:46,790
But Se Chan, it isn't you.

413
00:29:46,790 --> 00:29:48,540
It isn't you.

414
00:29:48,540 --> 00:29:53,510
If not me, did you do it, Grandma?

415
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:57,570
Oh dear, how can you say that?

416
00:29:57,570 --> 00:30:00,410
Aigoo. Aigoo.

417
00:30:00,410 --> 00:30:03,850
I'm telling you the truth. I did it.

418
00:30:05,900 --> 00:30:07,760
Ms. Park. Ms. Park!

419
00:30:07,760 --> 00:30:08,880
Ms. Park!

420
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:13,060
Se Chan, you stay here. I will go see her.

421
00:30:13,070 --> 00:30:15,520
What kind of craziness is this?

422
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:18,780
How can you brutally accuse someone innocent?

423
00:30:34,850 --> 00:30:39,310
Se Chan, can we talk?

424
00:30:39,310 --> 00:30:42,070
About what?

425
00:30:42,070 --> 00:30:46,950
Se Chan, lying is wrong.

426
00:30:46,950 --> 00:30:49,630
Lying begets new lies.

427
00:30:49,630 --> 00:30:55,220
And those lies could create something you can't manage later.

428
00:30:55,220 --> 00:31:00,650
Chief Jo, why are you talking to me like this all of a sudden?

429
00:31:00,650 --> 00:31:04,440
Did you really pick up that necklace?

430
00:31:04,440 --> 00:31:07,420
Did you really put it in Ms. Park's drawer?

431
00:31:07,420 --> 00:31:10,500
- Yes.
- Se Chan!

432
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:13,310
Lying is wrong, I said.

433
00:31:13,310 --> 00:31:15,990
Why do you keep saying I am lying?

434
00:31:15,990 --> 00:31:19,910
Are you saying you know who put the necklace

435
00:31:19,910 --> 00:31:23,050
in Ms. Park's drawer, Chief Jo?

436
00:31:24,400 --> 00:31:27,440
- What?
- I have to do my homework.

437
00:31:27,440 --> 00:31:29,970
Please get out!

438
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:35,390
I know you're lying!

439
00:31:35,390 --> 00:31:38,830
You didn't put it in the drawer!

440
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:44,600
Seriously.

441
00:31:49,870 --> 00:31:55,260
Okay. Do your homework.

442
00:32:07,510 --> 00:32:10,820
What did Se Chan say? Why did he lie?

443
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:12,870
He said he didn't lie.

444
00:32:12,870 --> 00:32:17,250
He kept on insisting that he did it.

445
00:32:17,250 --> 00:32:21,520
But I'm the one who put it in the drawer, so why is he saying it was him?

446
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:26,500
Se Chan is doing that to protect Ms. Park, isn't he?

447
00:32:26,500 --> 00:32:28,290
I think so.

448
00:32:28,290 --> 00:32:32,870
What drugs did Ms. Park feed them for the children to love her that much?

449
00:32:32,870 --> 00:32:38,750
You saw it yourself, Madam. Ms. Park is not ordinary. We've all been fooled!

450
00:32:38,750 --> 00:32:41,830
Right, she's not an ordinary vixen.

451
00:32:41,830 --> 00:32:45,720
She has at least nine tails.

452
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:50,540
We have to get her out here quick, or there will be big trouble.

453
00:33:03,450 --> 00:33:06,190
Ms. Park!

454
00:33:10,450 --> 00:33:14,010
Young Gook, haven't you found her yet?

455
00:33:14,010 --> 00:33:18,760
No, she didn't take her phone, so I can't even call her.

456
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:23,520
I'll go this way. Let's call each other when one of us finds her.

457
00:33:23,520 --> 00:33:25,950
Okay.

458
00:34:00,500 --> 00:34:04,120
Yes, Noona. I found Ms. Park.

459
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:08,380
I will bring her home. So please go in first.

460
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:14,050
Okay. Please talk to her nicely and bring her home.

461
00:34:21,230 --> 00:34:22,660
Oh, my head.

462
00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:24,370
Here's some ice water, Madam.

463
00:34:24,370 --> 00:34:29,910
I think the shock was too much for me. The fever won't go down.

464
00:34:29,910 --> 00:34:32,440
Oh, my goodness.

465
00:34:34,410 --> 00:34:38,550
Madam, how can you do that?

466
00:34:38,550 --> 00:34:41,620
How can you accuse someone of stealing so hastily?

467
00:34:41,620 --> 00:34:44,400
Is this how you've been treating your employees all along?

468
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:48,110
My goodness, CEO Anna.

469
00:34:48,110 --> 00:34:51,340
Why are you speaking to me like that, with your eyes glaring?

470
00:34:51,340 --> 00:34:54,730
She's in a strangers' house as a live-in tutor to make some money.

471
00:34:54,730 --> 00:34:57,760
How can you accuse a helpless young lady like that of stealing?

472
00:34:57,760 --> 00:35:00,730
- Is that something a human being should do?
- Excuse me, CEO Anna.

473
00:35:00,730 --> 00:35:04,390
Are you scolding me right now? Who do you think you are?

474
00:35:04,390 --> 00:35:08,180
Are you related to Ms. Park or something?

475
00:35:08,180 --> 00:35:11,210
Just think if Ms. Park was your daughter.

476
00:35:11,210 --> 00:35:14,470
How would you feel if Se Ryun was accused of stealing by someone?

477
00:35:14,470 --> 00:35:17,560
This is not the way to live a life!

478
00:35:17,560 --> 00:35:19,940
You leave me speechless.

479
00:35:19,940 --> 00:35:24,130
Did I do it for no reason? I found my necklace in her room!

480
00:35:24,130 --> 00:35:27,130
How dare you lecture me? Please pack up your bags and leave this house!

481
00:35:27,130 --> 00:35:29,560
How dare a guest to speak to me this way?

482
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:33,720
Why would I get out? Are you the owner of this house?

483
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:37,320
Oh my, this woman is crazy!

484
00:35:37,320 --> 00:35:40,560
You are the crazy one!

485
00:35:40,560 --> 00:35:44,500
From now on, don't treat the employees carelessly.

486
00:35:44,500 --> 00:35:48,010
Whoever it is, Ms. Park, Mrs. Yeoju, Chief Jo, or Driver Kang.

487
00:35:48,010 --> 00:35:50,550
Do you get that?

488
00:35:53,090 --> 00:35:55,870
That woman! I'm going to get her!

489
00:35:55,870 --> 00:35:59,060
Madam! Please, calm down.

490
00:35:59,060 --> 00:36:02,470
There's nothing good getting on the bad side of CEO Anna.

491
00:36:02,470 --> 00:36:07,430
Chairman Lee listens to every word she says.

492
00:36:07,430 --> 00:36:14,150
Not Ms. Park, but I need to kick that woman out first! It's infuriating.

493
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:18,710
It's crazy. That woman is crazy!

494
00:36:58,590 --> 00:37:02,270
Ms. Park, are you okay?

495
00:37:06,520 --> 00:37:11,160
Ms. Park, I'm sorry.

496
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:15,080
I don't know how this could have happened.

497
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:19,170
Let me apologize on behalf of everyone.

498
00:37:19,170 --> 00:37:23,160
Since the necklace came out from my desk,

499
00:37:23,160 --> 00:37:27,860
I understand how Madam could have misunderstood.

500
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:33,080
But still, it's very upsetting.

501
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:37,740
No one in my family thinks you would do something like that.

502
00:37:37,740 --> 00:37:40,140
They are all on your side.

503
00:37:40,140 --> 00:37:42,790
You must know that, right?

504
00:37:45,550 --> 00:37:48,270
Yes.

505
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:53,770
Then, let's go back together. Everyone is worried.

506
00:37:53,770 --> 00:37:57,410
I want to stay out a little longer.

507
00:37:57,410 --> 00:38:02,280
Please go back home first, and don't worry about me.

508
00:38:09,170 --> 00:38:14,070
Okay, then please come home soon.

509
00:38:14,070 --> 00:38:16,580
Yes.

510
00:38:39,170 --> 00:38:41,830
Ms. Park!

511
00:38:44,570 --> 00:38:47,630
Get on.

512
00:38:47,630 --> 00:38:50,380
Chairman.

513
00:38:50,380 --> 00:38:52,240
