570
00:43:45,380 --> 00:43:49,120
I saw it with my own eyes!

571
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:55,370
But why didn't you say that earlier?

572
00:43:55,370 --> 00:43:58,300
It's because she's still my Grandmother.

573
00:43:58,300 --> 00:44:01,710
If I say Grandma did it in front of everyone,

574
00:44:01,710 --> 00:44:03,850
she'll be embarrassed,

575
00:44:03,850 --> 00:44:05,860
and things might get bigger.

576
00:44:05,860 --> 00:44:10,240
That's why I wanted to tell the truth, but I couldn't.

577
00:44:10,260 --> 00:44:15,100
But I felt like she shouldn't get away with it.

578
00:44:15,100 --> 00:44:18,050
She did something bad to Ms. Park,

579
00:44:18,050 --> 00:44:22,160
so even if she's my grandma, she still has to be punished!

580
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:27,220
I thought if I didn't punish her, she'd be mean to Ms. Park again.

581
00:44:29,830 --> 00:44:32,190
Okay, Se Chan.

582
00:44:32,190 --> 00:44:36,860
Thank you for being honest with me.

583
00:44:36,860 --> 00:44:40,120
But, Se Chan.

584
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:45,010
If something like this happens again, trust me and tell me first.

585
00:44:45,010 --> 00:44:48,560
Can you do that?

586
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:50,970
Yes.

587
00:44:50,980 --> 00:44:53,480
How!

588
00:44:53,480 --> 00:44:56,960
How can you do that!

589
00:44:57,000 --> 00:45:02,330
What did I do for you to shout at me like that?

590
00:45:02,330 --> 00:45:05,260
Do you really not know?

591
00:45:05,260 --> 00:45:06,920
I don't know!

592
00:45:06,920 --> 00:45:11,690
I almost had a heart attack while I was sleeping! Why are you shouting at me!

593
00:45:11,690 --> 00:45:19,040
Se Chan saw you hiding the necklace in Ms. Park's room!

594
00:45:19,040 --> 00:45:21,240
Why on earth did you do that?

595
00:45:21,240 --> 00:45:22,720
Why?

596
00:45:22,720 --> 00:45:26,260
What kind of grudge do you hold against Ms. Park to do that?

597
00:45:26,260 --> 00:45:30,990
T-That's because...

598
00:45:30,990 --> 00:45:37,000
That's because... Kyung Sook?

599
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:41,870
I did it because she looks like Kyung Sook! Why else?

600
00:45:41,870 --> 00:45:45,060
She looks like Kyung Sook, that damn woman who seduced your father!

601
00:45:45,060 --> 00:45:49,550
That's why I did it! Why else?

602
00:45:49,550 --> 00:45:52,900
Kyung Sook? Who is Kyung Sook?

603
00:45:52,900 --> 00:45:54,330
Who is that?

604
00:45:54,330 --> 00:45:59,830
My housekeeper! The girl who worked in my house, you know her!

605
00:45:59,830 --> 00:46:02,060
What are you saying?!

606
00:46:02,060 --> 00:46:03,760
That kind of person didn't exist!

607
00:46:03,760 --> 00:46:07,620
There was, there was! Kyung Sook, Kyung Sook, Kyung Sook!

608
00:46:07,620 --> 00:46:13,100
She seduced your father, so I had such a hard time! That Kyung Sook!

609
00:46:13,100 --> 00:46:15,550
Pardon me?

610
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,980
Do you think we should test her for dementia?

611
00:46:21,980 --> 00:46:26,570
Yes! I think Madam's acting strange.

612
00:46:26,570 --> 00:46:28,900
She's a bit young to have dementia.

613
00:46:28,900 --> 00:46:30,620
No, Young Gook!

614
00:46:30,620 --> 00:46:32,770
There's a lot of people who have dementia at that age these days.

615
00:46:32,770 --> 00:46:34,800
Does this make sense unless she's sick?

616
00:46:34,800 --> 00:46:40,100
They say people do ridiculous things when they have dementia!

617
00:46:40,100 --> 00:46:42,370
Now that I think about it, I think you're right.

618
00:46:42,370 --> 00:46:45,400
There was never a person called Kyung Sook in our household.

619
00:46:45,400 --> 00:46:49,740
Make sure she gets checked up, okay? Before it gets worse.

620
00:46:52,540 --> 00:46:54,130
What just happened?

621
00:46:54,130 --> 00:46:58,020
Who is Kyung Sook? Why did that name jump out of me?!

622
00:46:58,020 --> 00:47:02,740
Oh, how embarrassing! Everyone must think I'm mad!

623
00:47:02,740 --> 00:47:04,280
Wait.

624
00:47:04,280 --> 00:47:06,820
That's right. Being mad is better!

625
00:47:06,820 --> 00:47:11,030
It's better to be considered a crazy person than kicked out of this house in shame.

626
00:47:11,030 --> 00:47:13,370
Oh, how embarrassing. Oh!

627
00:47:15,260 --> 00:47:20,820
It's Chrysanthemum tea. Drinking it makes you feel at peace and lets you sleep better.

628
00:47:20,820 --> 00:47:24,320
Here. Take a sip.

629
00:47:24,320 --> 00:47:27,030
Thank you.

630
00:47:29,680 --> 00:47:37,250
Ms. Park. You were shocked and saddened today, weren't you?

631
00:47:37,250 --> 00:47:41,710
We've decided to get Madam tested for dementia tomorrow.

632
00:47:41,710 --> 00:47:44,230
A dementia test?

633
00:47:44,230 --> 00:47:47,690
I think the Madam's ill.

634
00:47:47,690 --> 00:47:50,440
So, about what happened today,

635
00:47:50,440 --> 00:47:53,070
