00:57:52,940 --> 00:57:58,520
This is my younger brother Kyung Hoon. It's him!

771
00:57:58,520 --> 00:58:00,450
Oh, my goodness.

772
00:58:00,450 --> 00:58:03,080
Oh, how could such a wonderful event happen?

773
00:58:03,080 --> 00:58:06,590
Oh, my brother!

774
00:58:06,590 --> 00:58:09,400
Where's my brother?

775
00:58:09,400 --> 00:58:11,480
Where's my younger brother, Kyung Hoon?

776
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:14,960
Let's go right now. Right now!

777
00:58:23,390 --> 00:58:25,780
Here.

778
00:58:33,670 --> 00:58:37,100
Kyung Hoon.

779
00:58:37,100 --> 00:58:41,430
Are you Kyung Hoon?

780
00:58:41,430 --> 00:58:43,230
Kyung Hoon?

781
00:58:43,230 --> 00:58:48,100
Right, your name when you were little was Kyung Hoon.

782
00:58:49,720 --> 00:58:52,100
Oh, my gosh!

783
00:58:52,100 --> 00:58:57,100
He looks just like our father, who passed away!

784
00:58:59,000 --> 00:59:03,820
Can you recognize me? I'm your older sister!

785
00:59:09,470 --> 00:59:12,700
Look at this picture.

786
00:59:12,700 --> 00:59:17,490
It's a picture we took when we were little!

787
00:59:23,280 --> 00:59:26,700
This is...

788
00:59:26,700 --> 00:59:30,170
This is me! Me!

789
00:59:30,170 --> 00:59:34,650
Yes! You're right. It's you!

790
00:59:34,650 --> 00:59:41,590
Kyung Hoon, do you know how long I've searched for you, Kyung Hoon?

791
00:59:41,590 --> 00:59:44,930
Oh, Kyung Hoon!

792
00:59:44,930 --> 00:59:47,930
Kyung Hoon!

793
00:59:47,930 --> 00:59:50,290
Noona...

794
00:59:50,290 --> 00:59:55,480
Kyung Hoon! Kyung Hoon!

795
00:59:55,480 --> 00:59:59,030
Oh, my little brother, Kyung Hoon!

796
00:59:59,050 --> 01:00:02,080
Kyung Hoon!

797
01:00:06,010 --> 01:00:09,360
Kyung Hoon!

798
01:00:39,400 --> 01:00:43,030
Park Dan Dan. Come to your senses.

799
01:00:44,160 --> 01:00:47,680
Dad's calling.

800
01:00:47,680 --> 01:00:50,400
Did something happen?

801
01:00:52,340 --> 01:00:55,690
Yes, Dad.

802
01:00:55,690 --> 01:00:57,490
What?

803
01:00:57,490 --> 01:01:00,660
What did you just say?

804
01:01:00,680 --> 01:01:02,470
What?

805
01:01:02,470 --> 01:01:05,740
You found your older sister?!

806
01:01:17,320 --> 01:01:20,420
Is this where you live?

807
01:01:20,420 --> 01:01:26,710
Yes. It'll go through re-development soon, so it's a bit old, but it's comfortable to live.

808
01:01:26,710 --> 01:01:28,610
Yes!

809
01:01:28,610 --> 01:01:30,090
Who is this?

810
01:01:30,090 --> 01:01:33,770
This is my son, Noona.

811
01:01:33,770 --> 01:01:36,680
Hello, my name is Park Dae Beom.

812
01:01:36,680 --> 01:01:41,070
Oh, my... You're my Kyung Hoon's son.

813
01:01:41,070 --> 01:01:46,620
My gosh, you're exactly the same as when my Kyung Hoon was young!

814
01:01:46,620 --> 01:01:53,040
My mom would have been so happy if she saw you, Dae Beom.

815
01:01:53,040 --> 01:01:55,840
- Dad!
- Oh, Dan Dan! Welcome.

816
01:01:55,840 --> 01:01:58,050
Noona... She's my daughter.

817
01:01:58,050 --> 01:02:00,820
Your daughter?

818
01:02:00,820 --> 01:02:04,280
Hello, my name is Park Dan Dan.

819
01:02:04,280 --> 01:02:07,830
You grew up so well and pretty.

820
01:02:09,490 --> 01:02:16,120
Our Dae Beom... My mom should have seen you before she passed away.

821
01:02:19,140 --> 01:02:21,830
Oh!

822
01:02:21,830 --> 01:02:23,570
Who's this now?

823
01:02:23,570 --> 01:02:26,530
Oh, that's my son.

824
01:02:26,530 --> 01:02:29,430
Hello, Madam Sister-in-law.

825
01:02:29,430 --> 01:02:31,330
"Madam Sister-in-law?"

826
01:02:31,330 --> 01:02:34,020
Oh, you punk. Why would you call her 'Madam?'

827
01:02:34,020 --> 01:02:37,060
You need to call her 'Sister-in-law.'

828
01:02:37,060 --> 01:02:41,950
It's all right. There's nothing wrong with 'Madam Sister-in-law.'

829
01:02:51,650 --> 01:02:56,160
H-hyungnim... I didn't prepare much, but I hope you enjoy it.

830
01:02:56,160 --> 01:02:57,950
Hyungnim...

831
01:02:57,950 --> 01:03:00,820
I have a sister-in-law now.

832
01:03:00,820 --> 01:03:04,790
Thank you for the food, sister-in-law.

833
01:03:04,790 --> 01:03:11,170
Thanks to reuniting with my Kyung Hoon, I get to be called 'Hyungnim.'

834
01:03:11,170 --> 01:03:13,540
My son-in-law's name is Soo Chul.

835
01:03:13,540 --> 01:03:16,730
Don't you think you'll have to call him Soo Chul now?

836
01:03:16,730 --> 01:03:19,230
Oh... That's right.

837
01:03:19,230 --> 01:03:23,940
I shouldn't call you Kyung Hoon anymore and call you Soo Chul from now.

838
01:03:23,940 --> 01:03:27,740
Let's all lift our glasses and toast!

839
01:03:27,740 --> 01:03:30,560
Yes, Noona!

840
01:03:30,570 --> 01:03:34,720
My Joon Oh should've come to this happy gathering too.

841
01:03:34,720 --> 01:03:38,860
But he's going to medical school outside of Seoul. He'll come next weekend.

842
01:03:38,860 --> 01:03:41,380
I'll make sure to bring him that time, and we'll gather together.

843
01:03:41,380 --> 01:03:45,420
Let's do that! The doctor is busy with his studies.

844
01:03:45,420 --> 01:03:48,910
We have a doctor in our family now!

845
01:03:48,910 --> 01:03:52,450
Let's toast to us becoming one family!

846
01:03:52,450 --> 01:03:55,270
- Let's all toast together!
- All right, then...

847
01:03:55,270 --> 01:03:59,760
Let's celebrate my brother-in-law and sister-in-law reuniting. Let's all cheers to that!

848
01:03:59,760 --> 01:04:02,750
Cheers!

849
01:04:12,430 --> 01:04:16,720
Mom... Are you watching from heaven?

850
01:04:16,720 --> 01:04:22,350
I found our Kyung Hoon. Our Kyung Hoon!

851
01:04:23,680 --> 01:04:29,480
Kyung Hoon... Until right before our mom passed,

852
01:04:29,480 --> 01:04:33,220
she only kept calling your name and then passed away.

853
01:04:33,220 --> 01:04:38,190
- Did our mom do that?
- Yes.

854
01:04:38,190 --> 01:04:43,910
Our mom must be so happy now.

855
01:04:45,740 --> 01:04:50,550
Mom... I...

856
01:04:50,550 --> 01:04:53,440
Our Kyung Hoon's hand...

857
01:04:53,440 --> 01:04:56,970
I'll never let it go anymore.

858
01:05:03,610 --> 01:05:06,980
So, Mom...

859
01:05:06,980 --> 01:05:10,970
Rest in peace up there.

860
01:05:15,080 --> 01:05:17,710
Mom...

861
01:05:27,890 --> 01:05:29,240
- Why don't you have some meat?
- Let's eat!

862
01:05:29,240 --> 01:05:31,430
Let's eat a lot!

863
01:05:41,290 --> 01:05:43,720
It's so late.

864
01:05:43,720 --> 01:05:47,660
Ms. Park doesn't even have a car. When does she plan on coming?

865
01:06:14,790 --> 01:06:17,200
Chairman!

866
01:06:19,100 --> 01:06:20,480
You're a bit late.

867
01:06:20,480 --> 01:06:23,710
I'm sorry... I'm a little late.

868
01:06:23,710 --> 01:06:26,050
Did you meet your Aunt well?

869
01:06:26,050 --> 01:06:29,600
Yes, I did!

870
01:06:29,600 --> 01:06:32,570
My eyes are so swollen today, aren't they?

871
01:06:32,570 --> 01:06:35,390
Our entire family was crying so much today.

872
01:06:35,390 --> 01:06:40,310
We cried and then laughed, then laughed and cried...

873
01:06:40,310 --> 01:06:42,940
I sincerely congratulate that you found your aunt.

874
01:06:42,940 --> 01:06:45,380
Thank you, Chairman.

875
01:06:45,380 --> 01:06:48,900
I'm so happy today.

876
01:06:48,900 --> 01:06:54,270
It's been so long since my dad was that happy.

877
01:06:54,270 --> 01:06:58,350
So, because I was so happy,

878
01:06:58,350 --> 01:07:03,520
I had just one drink! Just one!

879
01:07:03,520 --> 01:07:05,890
I don't think it was one drink.

880
01:07:05,890 --> 01:07:09,280
You're right... It wasn't one.

881
01:07:09,280 --> 01:07:11,690
I drank quite a lot.

882
01:07:11,690 --> 01:07:18,410
Please understand me, Chairman. If not on a day like this, when will I get to drink?

883
01:07:18,410 --> 01:07:21,520
All right, I will understand. Let's go in now.

884
01:07:21,520 --> 01:07:24,490
Thank you!

885
01:07:44,160 --> 01:07:48,760
I'm sorry. I thought you were going to fall.

886
01:07:55,780 --> 01:07:58,510
Chairman...

887
01:07:58,510 --> 01:08:02,050
Why are you being so nice to me?

888
01:08:02,050 --> 01:08:03,610
Excuse me?

889
01:08:03,610 --> 01:08:07,110
Because you keep being so nice to me,

890
01:08:07,110 --> 01:08:11,790
my heart feels like it's going to explode!

891
01:08:14,880 --> 01:08:16,600
What did you say?

892
01:08:16,600 --> 01:08:21,450
I think...

893
01:08:21,450 --> 01:08:23,670
I like you, Chairman.

894
01:08:23,670 --> 01:08:28,890
Whenever I see you, my heart keeps pounding and making a fuss.

895
01:08:28,890 --> 01:08:32,310
Chairman, what if I get heart disease from this?

896
01:08:32,310 --> 01:08:37,760
If I get heart disease, will you take responsibility?

897
01:08:47,090 --> 01:08:53,890
♫ A smile blooms in every step ♫

898
01:08:53,890 --> 01:08:58,580
♫ It's a shiny day because of you ♫

899
01:08:58,580 --> 01:09:00,700
♫  It's sunshine day ♫

900
01:09:00,700 --> 01:09:07,700
♫ Strangely, I'm drawn to you ♫

901
01:09:07,700 --> 01:09:14,120
♫ Nobody will understand me. You're the only one that I was looking for ♫

902
01:09:14,120 --> 01:09:22,440
♫ Woo, it's a happy day like a dream, yeah ♫

903
01:09:22,440 --> 01:09:25,920
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

904
01:09:25,920 --> 01:09:31,280
I won't tell you to take responsibility for my heart, Chairman.

905
01:09:31,280 --> 01:09:34,450
If the Chairman asks about the Alzheimer's test result...

906
01:09:34,450 --> 01:09:39,650
Seriously... Just tell him I just have a little bit.

907
01:09:39,650 --> 01:09:44,320
- We see again.
- What is Ms. Se Ryun going to do with that two-timing guy?

908
01:09:44,320 --> 01:09:48,080
- It's for you to eat when you're hungry.
- Thank you, Ms. Park. Oh...

909
01:09:48,080 --> 01:09:51,720
How could he call me, Ms. Park? How could he...

910
01:09:51,720 --> 01:09:54,410
I'll take care of it.

911
01:09:54,410 --> 01:09:58,340
If I were a real Alzheimer's patient, I would do something ridiculous and kick her out.

912
01:09:58,340 --> 01:10:00,340
- That's it!
- That's it!

913
01:10:00,340 --> 01:10:03,440
Madam. I brought your juice.

914
01:10:03,440 --> 01:10:08,180
You wench who deserves to die! You, evil wench!
